My meme

Background
I used to be afraid of dogs until I saw my friends beautiful golden retriever named little gray. Since then I am in love with dogs, especially golden retrievers.
This meme hopes to encourage more people to make friends with dogs by showing how adorable Golden Retreaters can be. 

library(magick)

# Get images form the internet
dog1 <- image_read("https://paradepets.com/.image/ar_1:1%2Cc_fill%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_1200/MTkxMzY1Nzg4NjczMzIwNTQ2/cutest-dog-breeds-jpg.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(300)
dog2 <- image_read("https://www.pdinsurance.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/taylor-sondgeroth-ltsKOg_q_Gc-unsplash-1.webp") %>%
  image_scale(300)

# Creat a blank square next to the "dogs image"

blank1 <- image_blank(width = 300,
                      height = 50,
                      color = '#CCFBFF'
) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "I love Golden Retriever",
                 gravity = "center",
                 size = 24,
                 font = "Times New Roman")


# Combine images
picture <- c(blank1, dog1, dog2)


# Create Meme
meme <- image_append(picture, stack = TRUE) 
meme


# Save meme
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png", format = "png")

My animated GIF

Background
The Lion King produced by Walt Disney is one of my favorite animations. Does anyone love this movie? 

library(magick)


# Get iamges of lion king from the website
lion1 <- image_read("https://prod-ripcut-delivery.disney-plus.net/v1/variant/disney/764F2A9B9CD5A8601381942F2A8C582ED593E88B0492E6776783FC64408E8ADC/scale?width=1200&aspectRatio=1.78&format=jpeg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

lion2 <- image_read("https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/ZjsT7zNH6VZqWnAXnSBVE6-1200-80.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

lion3 <- image_read("https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcS3MqGA9mjru6Vhprj7Sk0BPcg5t0jaj8LTEA&usqp=CAU") %>%
  image_scale(500)

lion4 <- image_read("https://cdn.disneyanimation.com/uploads/films/the-lion-king/log-walk-grown.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)


# Create a vector of lion king's images
lions <- c(lion1, lion2, lion3, lion4)


# Create animations of lion king's images and save it
animation <- image_animate(lions, fps=1) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "I love Lion King", 
                 color = "#8F3A3A00", 
                 size = 20, 
                 gravity = "north") 

animation

image_write(animation, "lion_king.gif", format = "gif")

Thanks for reviewing my first project!
